cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses decision forests and their performance on structured data lying on a manifold, such as images, text, and speech. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on improving the performance of decision forests on structured data, which is a common problem in these fields.
